***Functional Features Implemented
***All core functions of the system must be implemented and working according to the project requirements.

1. User Management
    - Patients, Doctors, and Admin can successfully register an account.  
    - Users can log in and log out securely.
    - The system correctly distinguishes between different user roles.

2. Appointment Management
    - Patients can select hospital departments.
    - Patients can choose available date and time slots
    - Patients can view their upcoming and completed appointments.
    - Patients can cancel appointments when necessary.
    - The system prevents double booking for the same time slot.
    - The system sends appointment confirmation notifications.

3. Queue Management
    - The system automatically generates queue numbers.
    - Patients can view the current queue status.
    - The system displays estimated waiting time.

4. Automated Notifications
    - Patients receive push notifications or alerts when their turn is approaching.

5. Admin Dashboard
    - Admin can manage departments.
    - Admin can view and manage appointment records.
    - Admin can view daily patient numbers.
    - Admin can view total daily appointments.
    - Admin can view the total number of staff members.

6. Doctor Dashboard
   - Doctors can view and manage appointment records.
   - Doctors can see daily patient numbers.
   - Doctors can see daily appointment counts.

***Non-Functional Requirements Met

1. Security
   - User passwords are encrypted before being stored in the database.
   - Only authorized users can access admin functions.

2. Performance
  - System pages load within 3 seconds under normal conditions.
  - The system supports at least 100 concurrent users in the prototype environment.

3. Usability
   - The interface is simple, clear, and easy to navigate.
   - The application works on mobile devices and desktop browsers.

4. Reliability
   - The system is accessible at all times during testing and demonstration.
   - Appointment data is automatically saved and stored in the database.

5. Maintainability
   - The system uses modular and object-oriented design.
   - Departments and schedules can be updated easily without major code changes.

***Testing and Quality Assurance
Before a feature is considered complete:
   - All functions are tested by the development team.
   - Major bugs or system crashes are fixed.
   - Key workflows (register → login → book appointment → queue tracking) operate successfully.
   - The system is ready for prototype demonstration.

***Documentation Completed
The prototype is considered done when:
   - System functional requirements and non-functional requirements are documented.
   - User roles and system features are clearly explained.
   - Screenshots or UI demonstrations are prepared for the final presentation or report.

***Prototype Demonstration Ready
The project is considered complete when:
   - The system can be demonstrated end-to-end:
   - Patient registers and books appointment
   - Queue number is generated
   - Doctor views appointment
   - Admin monitors system data
   - All main system features can be shown without errors during presentation.




